Welcome to May's Turing-Roche newsletter! Here you can find what's new in the Turing-Roche strategic partnership and opportunities, events and news from both The Alan Turing Institute and Roche.

Our [five year partnership](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FkJvIeoC-MNYHSoJzT1jhDQ&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C4695b495f1a84f749bd308da3351bc60%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C637878723410678255%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=AcQ2IdiK3GOcxfeNiB2jTSY8tUpnJXYH%2BTJ2iIpT5lY%3D&reserved=0) was set up officially in June 2021 following a successful [Data Study Group](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2Fj58W8XTrKy0T7SMwcy2tvg&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C4695b495f1a84f749bd308da3351bc60%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C637878723410678255%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=b3AGtIBYai8TJOAQL%2FxYEbcvsa1UVaHVLANSGoAyJys%3D&reserved=0) and a 12 week research project on lung cancer treatment. Our 'North Star' is **to enable the generation of insights to better understand patient and disease heterogeneity and its relevance to clinical outcomes at an unprecedented level of precision in order to improve clinical care.**

We will be covering multiple activities over the five years to work towards our North Star, as well as building strong connections and collaborations between the Alan Turing Institute, Roche and the wider community.

If you have anything you'd like featured in a future newsletter then please get in touch with Vicky Hellon, Community Manager for the partnership at <vhellon@turing.ac.uk>

If you would like to share this newsletter with relevant colleagues please direct them to sign-up [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FsYtV4fhRDxBaCmASksp_zw&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C4695b495f1a84f749bd308da3351bc60%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C637878723410678255%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=RgaZbRyyOL61iS9J9cudHDSGDJcMKNXd3rgWnOduxYI%3D&reserved=0).

### **Knowledge Share Series: Predictive Modelling in Healthcare**

**30 May 2022**

Join us for our newly launched [partnership knowledge share series](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FxiU8bTJCp3Ley7sZ1m_APg&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C4695b495f1a84f749bd308da3351bc60%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C637878723410678255%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=xwu4sIFGba%2Bv5s0BUfXqGJQJg%2Fjtb8G2WWS7z2r75X4%3D&reserved=0)! Our aim is to bring together members of the Turing and Roche networks and beyond to share different academic and industry perspectives on areas related to patient/treatment heterogeneity and data science more generally.

May's event is on the 30th and we'll be hearing from two Roche speakers and two Turing speakers on the topic of predictive modelling in healthcare. You can register for the event [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%_X2NsZGVlPU9Dc0U5RWtraXhPT2ZMTU1XRmlLLXQzUWxYdFQ3NDl4R1BvQmNyYUVKbTJVaXU5Vy1ZbDVWa2U1SDZmV0NHS0gmcmVjaXBpZW50aWQ9Y29udGFjdC00ODgwYThjMzkyM2NlYzExOGM2MjAwMjI0ODQzNGZlYi1hOGNjOWI3ZTkwMGE0NmYzYjExYWUzMGMyNGI1YzM5YyZlc2lkPWZkZTE5OGE2LTRiZDAtZWMxMS1hN2I1LTYwNDViZDBlOTljOSJ9%2FW_FIDuuEAA3rRkNGYu9AIg&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C4695b495f1a84f749bd308da3351bc60%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C637878723410678255%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=9DULQdDol3U9BnCgz%2FkwAlg0HtmpZpxYgm%2FsCtIqmog%3D&reserved=0).

### **Genomics England- Mind the Gap Piece**

The partnership has published an article on Genomics England's site Mind the Gap: Stories of Health Data Equity. The site publishes stories on different ideas, initiatives and perspectives to showcase the challenges of data diversity and that we need a diverse range of voices and efforts to meet this challenge.

You can check out our piece about the partnership and missing data written by Dr Alisha Davies, Dr Robin Mitra and Vicky Hellon [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FNBe7UaO7u-HEXDIkVXGCuQ&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C4695b495f1a84f749bd308da3351bc60%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C637878723410678255%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=YWGqN62kOiwKkIQGI46xUUl4%2FYqBfGG28wh3AHeeuF8%3D&reserved=0).

### **31st Bradford Hill Memorial Lecture: Beyond 'Standard-of-Care': novel trial designs for old problems**

**17 May 2022**

In conjunction with the Royal Statistical Society, the London School of Hygiene & Tropical Medicine are hosting Professor Sarah Walker, who will deliver the 31st Bradford Hill Memorial Lecture. She will be discussing the challenges posed by antimicrobial resistance- the need for diversity in prescribing counter to the single "standard-of-care" paradigm and requiring more challenging non-inferiority design. You can find out more [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%_X2NsZGVlPU9Dc0U5RWtraXhPT2ZMTU1XRmlLLXQzUWxYdFQ3NDl4R1BvQmNyYUVKbTJVaXU5Vy1ZbDVWa2U1SDZmV0NHS0gmcmVjaXBpZW50aWQ9Y29udGFjdC00ODgwYThjMzkyM2NlYzExOGM2MjAwMjI0ODQzNGZlYi1hOGNjOWI3ZTkwMGE0NmYzYjExYWUzMGMyNGI1YzM5YyZlc2lkPWZkZTE5OGE2LTRiZDAtZWMxMS1hN2I1LTYwNDViZDBlOTljOSJ9%2FK3u2sD8vTYI8MVH0oQMoTA&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C4695b495f1a84f749bd308da3351bc60%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C637878723410834469%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=%2FdXDesEAmn%2F2utV%2FsLKENPX9%2FLU0FlBC2AvS%2FG3YPew%3D&reserved=0).

### **The Royal Society of Medicine- Tackling Inequalities Conference**

**23 June 2022**

This inaugural conference, in partnership with NHS England and NHS Improvement, will focus on Core20PLUS5, an approach designed to support Integrated Care Systems to drive targeted action in healthcare inequalities improvement. This conference will have panel sessions in the morning and expert sessions in the afternoon, focusing on the five clinical areas of health inequalities and a session on prevention. You can find out more and register [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FETVjm5fIFdWRnUDFhVY-Kw&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C4695b495f1a84f749bd308da3351bc60%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C637878723410834469%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=Lthe9exQyXPdeWQ2qf%2FjByzFD%2BRbrgESS8%2FEiD%2BSpj8%3D&reserved=0).

## **Publication of the Month**

![](https://file-eu.clickdimensions.com/turingacuk-ap7zg/files/patrick-tomasso-oaqk7qqnh_c-unsplash2.jpg)

### **A robust and interpretable machine learning approach using multimodal biological data to predict future pathological tau accumulation**

Check out [this paper ](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%_%2FO21Yfi8dnZVhSzQ9bdQg9w&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C4695b495f1a84f749bd308da3351bc60%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C637878723410834469%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=YlpvRzBg6E4zHt%2B0cFT4cnsTjuJIt1MNUqufnJaop7g%3D&reserved=0)on early dementia prediction published in Nature Communications by our Expert Panel Member Zoe Kourtzi and her team. They employ a machine learning approach that successfully capitalises on longtiudinal data to make specific predictions of early stage Alzhemier's trajectories based on baseline pathophysiology.
